##Worried that the bill has "virus" , the old man unexpectedly microwave heating, more than 3000 yuan..

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

Suspecting that the Renminbi might be infected with the "new coronavirus" , aunt Li of Jiangyin, Wuxi, Jiangsu Province, recently put cash in a microwave oven to heat and sterilize it. More than 3,000 yuan was baked beyond recognition. So, how does the money disinfect exactly? Is it safe to use?

Recently, Aunt Li put the money into the microwave oven to sterilize it because she was worried that there was a virus on the money. Less than a minute later, the microwave oven wafted out the smell of burnt wood. Aunt Li hurriedly took out the cash, but it was too late, most of the paper money carbonized to black, and then want to spend it is impossible. Looking at the "burning coins" that had been roasted beyond recognition, Aunt Li was heartbroken and came to the Jiangyin branch of CITIC Bank for help.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Because "burning money" this damaged money is more special, carbonization part is more, can not distinguish through the instrument, the bank personnel can only by hand to identify the number and identify the authenticity, the operation is more difficult. In the process of counting, a touch of "burning money" on the drop of slag, in order to prevent secondary damage, need to carefully open, spread, and then stick the paper money on the same size white paper. After identification, inventory, confirmation, the bank for Aunt Li converted the full amount of the new 3125 yuan.

CITIC Bank Nanjing Branch of the relevant person in charge, in the current epidemic prevention and control of the special period, from the financial institutions out of the "clean money" , can be assured to use. In accordance with the requirements of the People's Bank of China, commercial banks withdraw cash from key areas for epidemic prevention and control, use ultraviolet radiation or high temperature disinfection, and store the cash for more than 14 days before putting it on the market, store for more than 7 days before putting on the market.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
So, in the special period of epidemic prevention and control, can people use cash with confidence?

The People's Bank of China and other relevant departments have made a series of arrangements to ensure the safety and hygiene of the People's use of cash. On the one hand, we have ensured the supply of new banknotes, suspended the inter-provincial transfer of cash and the intra-provincial transfer of cash in some areas where the epidemic is serious; on the other hand, we have strictly implemented the two lines of revenue and expenditure, and the temporary cash storage rooms for key units to be withdrawn, cash in circulation must be disinfected before it can be released.

Before January 17, the People's Bank of China had arranged for the allocation of nearly 600 billion yuan in new bank notes to the whole country, and the People's Bank of China had rushed to release 4 billion yuan in new bank notes to Wuhan before the Spring Festival.

The People's Bank of China (PBC) requires that foreign cash payments should be mainly made with new banknotes as far as possible, and that the cash returned from hospitals, agricultural markets and other channels should be treated in a special way and sealed separately when the cash is returned, after disinfection, deposited with the PBC and shall not be paid out.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
HOW DO BANKS STERILIZE CASH?

1. At the end of each day, bank teller to wear wipes the inside and outside of the box with 84 disinfectant, making sure that the box is dry before loading, so as to avoid dampness affecting the cash.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
2. Take an inventory of your cash receipts for the day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
3, after the count, the cash will be ultraviolet lamp irradiation disinfection, Disinfection Lamp Work Dot staff leave the scene, at the same time use alcohol or 84 disinfection solution to the cashier machine to wipe disinfection.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
4. Disinfect cash and put it in a separate cash box.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
5. The bank strictly checks the banknotes collected from key units such as hospitals, lengthens the disinfection time, disinfects and separates them separately, enters the accounts separately, Hands Over Them, inspects the packaging and marks with seals the words "hospital receipt" , etc. , set up a designated area to store the sterilized cash and ensure that it is not spent.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Experts remind, in the process of cash transfer may have personal contact, so need to do a good job of protection, develop the use of cash after washing hands and other good habits. Consumers can choose to pay by Bar Code, credit card and other non-cash payment methods to reduce the risk of epidemic spread.
